text: Wildwood is an unincorporated community in Lewis County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Wildwood was established in 1889, and remained in operation until 1930. The name Wildwood is descriptive of the original condition of the town site. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Lewis County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Wildwood, Washington
